Solution. By the local limit theorem

$$
\begin{aligned}
P_{t}(x)=\lim _{\Delta \rightarrow 0} \frac{P_{n \Delta}(k \sqrt{\Delta})}{\sqrt{\Delta}}=\lim _{\Delta \rightarrow 0} \frac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{\pi n \Delta\left(1 / 4-\Delta x^{2}\right)}} e^{-\frac{(k / 2-n \Delta x)^{2}}{2 n\left(1 / 4-\Delta x^{2}\right)}}= \\
=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{\pi t}} e^{-\frac{(x-2 t)^{2}}{2 t}}
\end{aligned}
$$

By direct calculation we obtain

$$
\begin{gathered}
\frac{\partial P_{t}(x)}{\partial t}=\frac{x^{2}-4 t^{2}-t}{t^{2} \sqrt{2 \pi t}} e^{-\frac{(x-2 t)^{2}}{2 t}}, \quad \frac{\partial P_{t}(x)}{\partial x}=-\frac{\sqrt{2}(x-2 t)}{t \sqrt{\pi t}} e^{-\frac{(x-2 t)^{2}}{2 t}} \\
\frac{\partial^{2} P_{t}(x)}{\partial x^{2}}=\frac{\sqrt{2}\left(x^{2}-4 t x+4 t^{2}-t\right)}{t^{2} \sqrt{\pi t}} e^{-\frac{(x-2 t)^{2}}{2 t}}
\end{gathered}
$$

By substitution we obtain that equation (*) is satisfied.

