(ii) $\lim _{x \rightarrow \infty} \frac{\ln f(x)}{\ln x}=a$.

3. Let $I_{n}=\int_{0}^{1} \frac{x^{n}}{x^{2}+1} d x, n \in \mathbb{N}^{*}$.

a) Show that $I_{n+2}+I_{n}=\frac{1}{n+1}$, for any $n \in \mathbb{N}^{*}$;

b) Show that $\frac{1}{2(n+1)} \leq I_{n} \leq \frac{1}{2(n-1)}$, for any $n \geq 2$;

c) Calculate $\lim _{n \rightarrow \infty} n I_{n}$.

original.solution:
3. a) Verify;

b) Apply the monotonicity of the integral and the previous point;

c) Apply the previous point and the squeeze theorem and we obtain $\lim _{n \rightarrow \infty} n l_{n}=\frac{1}{2}$

